# Scan an input file
src/scan-grib data/SAF_MSGEURO_CRR_20051205_0615.grb > test.md

# Dispatch a series of gribs given their metadata
src/store-grib -o testarc -s data test.md

Dependencies:

 libgrib-api-dev
   (optional, for importing grib1 and grib2)
 liblua-dev
   (optional, for importing grib1 and grib2)
 libdballepp-dev
   (optional, for importing bufr)
 libsqlite3-dev
   (mandatory, for the dataset indices)
 libcurl[...]-dev
   (optional, for querying remote datasets)
 python, python-configobj, python-cherrypy
   (optional, for the server.  I test in python 2.4, not sure if it would work
   in 2.3, most likely not as I use subprocess)

To pull in the embedded wibble, use this command:

 darcs init
 darcs pull -a http://people.debian.org/~enrico/wibble/embeddable

 Then just 'darcs pull' will get the new updates of wibble

If you don't have darcs, run this instead:

 wget http://people.debian.org/~enrico/wibble/embeddable/wibble.tar.gz
 tar zxf wibble.tar.gz
 mv wibble/wibble/* wibble/
